%N A396987 The number of n-colorings of the faces of the triakis tetrahedron up to rotation.
%C A396987 Colorings are counted up to the rotational tetrahedral group of order 12.
%C A396987 Also, the number of n-colorings of the vertices of the truncated tetrahedron, which is the polyhedral dual of the triakis tetrahedron.
%C A396987 Also, the number of n-colorings of the faces of the pyritohedron, which has 12 pentagonal faces and 20 vertices and is topologically equivalent to a dodecahedron.
%H A396987 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A396987/b396987.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1000</a>
%H A396987 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dodecahedron#Pyritohedron">Pyritohedron</a>.
%H A396987 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tetrahedral_symmetry">Tetrahedral symmetry</a>.
%H A396987 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Triakis_tetrahedron">Triakis tetrahedron</a>.
%H A396987 <a href="/index/Rec#order_13">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (13,-78,286,-715,1287,-1716,1716,-1287,715,-286,78,-13,1).
%F A396987 a(n) = (n^12 + 3*n^6 + 8*n^4)/12.
%t A396987 A396987[n_] := n^4*(n^8 + 3*n^2 + 8)/12; Array[A396987, 25, 0] (* _Paolo Xausa_, Jun 16 2026 *)
%Y A396987 Cf. A396858 (rotation and reflection).
%Y A396987 Cf. A128766 (octahedron), A199406 (rhombic dodecahedron), A252704 (icosahedron), A252705 (dodecahedron), A274900 (rhombicuboctahedron), A274901 (truncated cube), A337963 (rhombic triacontahedron), A378473 (tetrakis hexahedron), A378474 (disdyakis dodecahedron), A378475 (pentagonal icositetrahedron), A378476 (triakis icosahedron), A378477 (disdyakis triacontahedron), A378478 (pentagonal hexecontahedron), A378478 (pentagonal hexecontahedron), A395240 (bipyramids), A396861 (truncated icosahedron), A396913 (trapezohedron), A396986 (disdyakis dodecahedron).
